My one star is reference to the experience tonight, not overall. We've been ordering here for years, and LOVE the pie. Their primary weakness is estimating delivery time, even within a range.

Tonight was extreme. We placed order for the game (go Utes) and were quoted 30 mins. A full one hour later I called to see if they forgot about our order. The team member answered, "Free Wheeler, can you please hold?" Five mins & 30 mins later I hung up and called right back. I said, "dude, I was on hold for five and a half minutes". He replied, "oh, sorry we forgot". The reason for being an hour in and no pizza was, "...we had a lot of orders".

The order showed up 15 minutes later, and pizza was sort of warm. Also, order incorrect.

So, order to receipt of incorrect, little better than room temp, order was 1hr 15 mins, on a 30 min quote.

Wow.
Best pie in the city. Consistent and always timely.

My favorite spot. I always request extra oil and cheese on my garlic knots. I forgot this Time so when I picked up I asked if it was too late. The owner told me he could do it. He didn‚Äôt charge me for it. Appreciated this gesture

We called Free Wheeler Pizza from the airport after securing a rental car. We ordered 2 calzones and a 1/2 dozen garlic knots. The order came out nice and hot 2 minutes after we arrived and it was SOOO good! The price was very reasonable and the service was terrific.  My only disappointment is that we live about 1500 miles away. Much too far for fast delivery.
The bbq pulled pork special pizza was incredible. Your pizza makers rule. ‚ÄòZa is life.
Excellent service and fantastic quality pizza using fresh ingredients!

detailedReviews.author: C C
detailedReviews.text: The best! I try to stick with local business when I order pizza, and Free Wheeler has been consistently good for years. The prices are great. For the cost, you wouldn't expect the dough to be as good as it is. The sourdough crust is so good. It tastes just as good as those highfalutin shops (if not better). I don't usually eat my crusts, but I eat Free Wheeler's crusts. The toppings are fresh. They have items besides pizza on their menu: salads, calzones, cold and hot sandwiches, desserts and a good variety of beverages. Their calzones are delicious. You get to build your own. This shop offers affordable, quality food. This place blows all of those chain restaurants out of the water. You won't find cardboard crusts here! The people working for Free Wheeler are awesome. The staff have always been friendly and helpful. If you sign up for their text messages, they send you a lot of great deals and specials. They are my go-to pizza shop. Buy their food!

detailedReviews.author: Tyler Alden
detailedReviews.text:
Today I picked up my favorite pizza‚ÄîThe Big Wheel Combo from Free Wheeler‚Äîto enjoy in the park.
After dinner, I packed up the car and, needing a free hand, set the pizza box on the roof. Big mistake. A few blocks later, I realized my error.
I flipped a U turn and ran back, expecting the worst. But there it was on the ground‚Äîopen, yes‚Äîbut miracle of miracles, the wax paper had slid free, carrying my last two slices untouched.
Cars had run over (but not *on* my slices, a critical distinction). So yes, dear reader, I rescued those slices. And now, with no regrets, I‚Äôm eating my rooftop leftovers.
Long live Free Wheeler Pizza. The service is always great and the pizza never disappoints.

detailedReviews.text: I absolutely love them still having the option to just get a slice, I ordered delivery from you guys a couple times because of your artichoke heart toppings that are rare to find, but when I realized your building is really close to my work, I'm now going here instead of McDonald's, cause I'll actually finish what I eat and not feel sick after haha. I really love your pizza, and you've become a staple of my commute. I also don't drive, so places that I can use my e-scooter to get there pretty quick is very nice. I hope I don't weird you guys out from how often I'll order slices lol.

detailedReviews.author: Mick Huerta
detailedReviews.text: Pizza-tarians (oh, yes - it's a thing) will love this place! The in-house artisanal dough produced there is amazing! And Old Ovens cranking mondo heat deliver a great pizza - crisp under side, the cornicione/borda = "crust edge" is cooked perfectly and a joy to eat! OK, the trick is not to over-load with toppings and a ton of cheese, go simple - balance the toppings to crust ratio for a true pizza-tarian experience ... yes, there are posh places all over the valley. But give me a pizza shop that makes it own dough and has ancient ovens and sits in a neighborhood with experienced pizzaiolos at the helm. When in SLC, Give Me Free-Wheeler!
